  "details": "Kerberos is a network authentication protocol. It is designed to provide strong authentication for client/server applications by using secret-key cryptography.\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\\r\\n\\r\\n\r\nMIT Kerberos 5 (aka krb5) before 1.17.2 and 1.18.x before 1.18.3 allows unbounded recursion via an ASN.1-encoded Kerberos message because the lib/krb5/asn.1/asn1_encode.c support for BER indefinite lengths lacks a recursion limit.(CVE-2020-28196)\\r\\n\\r\\n",
